column2: All right! (Checking his watch) Yes!! From home to the hospital in under\nseven minutes! We did it!!'
(deadpan) Yes, the hard part is truly over.'
No, but come on, we\xc2\x92re off to a great start aren\xc2\x92t we? I knew\nI\xc2\x92d get you here fast, but this has got to be some kind of a record!'
Oh you made it!'
Hi! (Ross is stunned.)'
How are you doing?'
Wait a minute! How-how the hell did you beat us here?'
We took a cab. Did you guys walk?'
N\xc2\x85 No! We took a cab too, but I did test runs!'
Hi!'
Hey! You made it!'

Ross, you stay here and talk, I\xc2\x92m gonna go have a baby.'
Okay. Okay. (To the nurse behind the desk.) Umm hi, this is Rachel Green.\nI\xc2\x92m Ross Geller. We-we called from the car.'
Right! We have a semi-private labor room waiting for you. So in just a\nminute\xc2\x85'

Okay. Just give us a second. Ross! (They walk away from the desk.)'
Yeah?'
Give her some money.'
I really think they\xc2\x92re out of rooms.'
They\xc2\x92re not!! Ross, they\xc2\x92re just saving them for the important\npeople!! Okay?! What-what if I was the president?!'

Well then we\xc2\x92d be in a lot of trouble, you don\xc2\x92t know where any
countries are. (Rachel glares at him.) Okay. (He goes over to the desk followed by
Rachel.) Uh, say would you umm\xc2\x85 Would you mind checking again to see if any umm,

This is a hospital.'

(standing up) Okay. Y\xc2\x92know what? I\xc2\x92d have to say I really\ndon\xc2\x92t care for your tone. And this is not the only hospital in this city and we have\nno problem to\xc2\x97Whoa! (She starts a contraction) Oh gosh! Whoa!'

Yeah, it couldn\xc2\x92t hurt to look.'

Oh, okay.'

Thank you.'

Thank you very much.'
Thanks.'

Oh no-no, not at all.'
Don\xc2\x92t worry about it.'

Hi Julie.'
Hi.'

Hi! '
Oh hi Rachel.'
How are you?'
Hi. Is this your first?'
Yeah it is.'

That\xc2\x92s so sweet.'
Yeah.'
Oh.'

No nonsense! We\xc2\x92re all in this together.'
Yeah, we are going to share every moment of this with you. And I think\nwe\xc2\x92re gonna have some fun.'
Yeah.'
Oh, okay.'
Hey! Smile! (Points his camera at Ross and Rachel.)'
Oh no, I really don\xc2\x92t want any\xc2\x97(He takes the picture)\xc2\x97Oh!\nThank you. Oh. Oh Ross\xc2\x85'
What?'
Here comes another contraction.'

Look at this! (Takes another picture) There we go!'

Hey, you wanna see something?'
Sure! What?'
Umm, this is going to be fun. Watch me freak out Chandler. Honey?'
Yeah?'

Okay.'

Okay. I\xc2\x92ve been thinking about it too, and I, I think we\xc2\x92re\nready.'
What?! Are you kidding me?! You-you-you think we\xc2\x92re ready to have a\nbaby now?!'
Oh, this is fun.'
You\xc2\x92re ready to have a baby? My boy\xc2\x92s all grown up!'

Okay, just back off mister! Whoa. (Pause) \xc2\x91Cause I am ready\nto have a baby. I just want Joey to be the father.'
(voice all high and weird) What?! Are you crazy?!'
That\xc2\x92s it! Right there! Is all I wanted!'
I am so sorry. The doctor insisted on closing the curtain for the exam.'
Oh, that\xc2\x92s very\xc2\x97Really very-very okay.'
Julie\xc2\x92s cervix is dilated a seven centimeters, that\xc2\x92s about four\nfingers. The doctor let me feel it myself.'
Have you felt Rachel\xc2\x92s cervix Ross?'
(simultaneously as Ross) No, I don\xc2\x92t think we\xc2\x92ll be doing\nthat.'
(simultaneously as Rachel) We\xc2\x92re not gonna do that.'

Oh. Oh wait no.'

Oh good.'

I brought something that I want to give you, assuming of course\nthat you want it. (She holds up an engagement ring.)'

This is your grandmother\xc2\x92s engagement ring, I want you to give\nit to Rachel.'

Just hear me out!'
N-no! Okay? We\xc2\x92ve been through this! We\xc2\x92re not gonna get married\njust because she\xc2\x92s pregnant, okay?'
Honestly! Ross, this isn\xc2\x92t just some girl you picked up in a\nbar and humped. A child should have a family.'
Mom, y\xc2\x92know what? I-I can\xc2\x92t deal with this right now. I\xc2\x92m\nsorry\xc2\x85'

Gimmie! (Takes the ring and puts it in his coat pocket as Rachel enters\nthe hallway.)'
Hi!'
Oh hi dear!'

\xc2\x85she came and dragged me out of the labor room to ask me why I\xc2\x92m\nnot with Rachel.'

Okay, stop it! I can\xc2\x92t deal with this right now. I have to go have a\nbaby.'
Right. And with who again? (Ross exits.)'
God. He\xc2\x92s crazy! Why doesn\xc2\x92t he want to be with Rachel?'
I know!'

I mean seriously, she\xc2\x92s like the perfect woman. I mean I know she

New people.'
What happened to the Disgustingtons?'

They\xc2\x92re having their baby! It\xc2\x92s not fair Ross we got here\nfirst! Right after you left they wheeled her off into delivery. Oh but not before she gave\nme a juicy shot of little Jamie just crowning away.'

Well they have uh, some unusual pet names for each other. Including umm,\nevil bitch and uh, sick bastard. Oh God oh! Contraction!'

Ooh! Ow!!'
Are you looking at her?! '

Ross.'
What? What?'

What?!!'
I\xc2\x92m kidding. This is going to be fun.'

Period math?'
Yeah.'
Yeah.'

All right.'

I\xc2\x92m in the middle\xc2\x85 (The elevator door closes, cutting him off.)'

Clifford Burnett.'
Date of birth? '
November 16th, 1968.'
Age?'

No.'

(checking the list) Yes.'
Well uh if you must know I\xc2\x92m a widower.'
Oh that\xc2\x92s terrible. I\xc2\x92m-I\xc2\x92m really sorry.'
Yeah.'

No.'

No!'

(calling to the woman) This room\xc2\x92s available.'

he\xc2\x92s a lawyer!'
Uh Rach\xc2\x85'

OH\xc2\x85.MY\xc2\x85.GAWD!!! (Uh-huh, it\xc2\x92s Janice.)'
I\xc2\x85.can\xc2\x92t\xc2\x85.believe this!'

(entering, carrying a pillow) Hi sweetie!'

Hi! Hi sweetheart! This is my husband Sid, I don\xc2\x92t think\nyou\xc2\x92ve met him. Ross, Rachel, this is Sid. I nabbed him a year ago at the\ndermatologist\xc2\x92s office. Thank God for adult acne huh? (Does the laugh.)'

Oh!'
Oh there you go!'
I get it!'

No-no. We\xc2\x85'

Oh. Ah-uh.'

Oh.'

We could, or we can have sex in it.'
Well let me think about that, while I remove my pants!'

Chandler Bing!'
Jan-Janice!'

Okay I\xc2\x92ve got one for you, if you had too which one would you\nrather eat, a seeing eye dog or a talking gorilla?'
I\xc2\x92d have to say\xc2\x85the talking gorilla, because at least I can\nexplain to him that you\xc2\x92re making me eat him.'
Somebody went to college. Wow. (Cliff gets uncomfortable) What is it?\nI\xc2\x92m sorry. (She moves her arm, which was resting on the same pillow his leg is.)'
